story.storybody:
The exam date for AIMS Test for Management Admissions (ATMA) July 2016 has been announced by the Association of Indian Management Schools (AIMS). The online exam is scheduled to be conducted on July 24 for admission to Master of Business Administration (MBA) and Post Graduate Diploma in Management (PGDM) programmes offered at various institutes/universities for the commencing academic session 2016.

Eligibility criteria

Educational qualification:

Those who are interested in applying for this exam should have done graduation from any recognised institute.

Age limit:

Age of the candidates applying for this exam should be minimum 21 years.

Paper pattern

The test will carry 180 questions divided into six sections. The time duration of the exam will be three hours. The questions cover Analytical Reasoning, Quantitative, and Verbal skills. Each multiple-choice question is followed by four answers numbered 1,2,3 and 4. A question with multiple answers will be treated as incorrect and, therefore, a negative score of -0.25 will be given.

TEST CENTRES

Normally, ATMA is conducted in the following test centres:

Ahmedabad (Gandhi Nagar), Bengaluru, Bhubaneswar, New Delhi, Ghaziabad, Hyderabad, Indore, Jaipur, Kolhapur, Kolkata, Lucknow, Mumbai, Navi Mumbai, Nagpur, Nashik, Pune, Raipur, Ranchi, and Thane.
